Naval investigators boarded the battleship Iowa to find out the cause of Wednesday's gun  explosion during a training exercise.
They discarded the theory that red-hot debris left in  a gun's breech by earlier rounds sparked the blast, because none of No.
2 turret's guns  had been fired.
All casualties were at the turret's top.
Eleven men escaped from powder  magazines at its base.
No eyewitnesses survived.
A moratorium was placed on firing 16- inch guns.
The bodies of the 47 sailors killed were flown to the military mortuary at  Dover AFB.
President Bush will attend a memorial service Monday in Norfolk. 
